gomodel:SYNGO_3059  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Absence of Bai3 reduces CF-EPSCs what can be rescued lentivirus injection of WT Bai3 (Fig. 4); and C1qrl1 interaction with Bai3 is essential for the maintenance of CF synapse in adults (Fig. 5)\n\n28/5/2018 Pim\n- Authors show that:\n1) C1ql1-Bai3 Triggers Pruning of Surplus CFs in Adult Mice\n2) The C1ql1-Bai3 Interaction Is Required to Maintain CF Synapses\nAnd state: \"These results indicate that C1ql1 has dual functions: strengthening existing CF synapses and inducing the elimination of inactive synapses\". Experimental description: Here, we show that C1ql1, a member of the C1q family of proteins, is provided by climbing fibers (CFs) and serves as a crucial anterograde signal to determine and maintain the single-winner CF in the mouse cerebellum throughout development and adulthood. Abstract, p. 316" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-28" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3059" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

